Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel) and pop onto a
large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for drizzling}, then sprinkle over half
the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1/2%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder)
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the remaining @Thai Style Spice Mix{1/2%sachet},
@breadcrumbs{10%g} and the @salt{1/4%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs,
then add the @British Beef Mince{240%g}.

Season with pepper and mix together with your hands. Shape into mini sausage
shapes, 4 per person. Flatten to make koftas.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

When the wedges are halfway through cooking, pop the koftas onto a large baking
tray. Bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through,
~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything cooks, zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Next, trim the @cucumber{1/2}, then pop it onto a #cutting board{} and use a
#rolling pin{} to gently smack it a few times until split. Cut into roughly
2cm chunks.

In a large bowl, add a good squeeze of lime juice, the @sambal paste{10%g}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @soy sauce{15%ml}. Season and add
a generous pinch of @sugar{pinch}, then mix to combine. Add the cucumber to
the bowl. Toss to combine. Set aside.

> TIP: Keep the other half of the cucumber for another recipe.

In another small bowl, combine the lime zest and the @mayonnaise{1%tbsp}.

When the koftas are ready, drizzle over the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g} while they
are still on the baking tray and toss until evenly glazed.

Once cooked, share the sweet chilli beef koftas between your plates.

Serve the spicy potato wedges and smacked cucumber on the side, along with
the zesty mayo for dipping.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges and serve on the side for squeezing over.

Enjoy!